Europe's got the fae angle, the fairy courts and such. America's just got your clever ones that often end up getting hoisted by their own petard because they thought they were too clever. Basically the "I'm a genius - oh no" type.
Neither really had them turn into people as far as I'm aware, mostly had them in the "talking animal" category.
If you count Native American interpretation, some tribes had foxes play the role of Prometheus and bring the knowledge of fire to humans, but in most cases they were thieves, greedy and tricky. There was one fox woman who guided and tested her adopted grandson (the Cree tribe had her as his mother instead) on the way to being a hero. Silver Fox, which is female in some interpretations, played a role in the world's creation and taught people how to live (she is serious/wise as opposed to the coyote who is a dipshit and frivolous).
